<Layout title="Auction vs Private Treaty vs EOI in Brisbane: How to Choose | Daniel Gierach Property" description="A practical guide to choosing between auction, private treaty, and expressions of interest when selling property in Brisbane — when each method works best and how to decide." draft={draft}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between auction and private treaty in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Auction is a public, time-limited sale where registered bidders compete openly and the property sells unconditionally to the highest bidder above the reserve. Private treaty is a negotiated sale where the vendor sets an asking price and buyers submit offers, with conditions such as finance and building inspections typically included."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When is auction the better choice for selling in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Auction works best for properties with broad, competing buyer interest — character homes in tightly held suburbs, properties with distinctive features that are hard to price, and market conditions where buyer competition is strong. It also suits vendors who want a fixed timeline and the certainty of unconditional exchange on the day."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are expressions of interest (EOI) and when are they used?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Expressions of interest involve marketing a property without a disclosed price and inviting buyers to submit written offers by a set deadline. EOI is most commonly used for high-value or unique properties where a market price range is genuinely difficult to determine, or where the vendor wants maximum privacy and control over the process."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is private treaty cheaper than auction in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Private treaty does not involve auctioneer fees, but the total marketing investment is similar. The more meaningful question is which method is likely to produce the best net result for your specific property — not which has the lower upfront cost."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<article style="background:var(--color-surface-0);min-height:100vh;">

